<Window x:Class="SE_project_2025.About"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:SE_project_2025"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="About" Height="500" Width="800"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen"
        ResizeMode="NoResize">

    <Grid>
        <!-- Background Image -->
        <Image Source="images/home_background.jpg" Stretch="Fill" Panel.ZIndex="-1"/>

        <!-- Main Content Area -->
        <Border Background="Transparent" CornerRadius="10" Padding="20" Margin="60,60,60,60">
            <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                <StackPanel>
                    <TextBlock Text="About Shehr-e-Sukhan"
                               FontSize="24"
                               FontWeight="Bold"
                               Foreground="Black"
                               TextAlignment="Center"
                               Margin="0,0,0,20"/>

                    <TextBlock FontSize="16"
                               Foreground="Black"
                               TextWrapping="Wrap"
                               TextAlignment="Justify">
Shehr-e-Sukhan is a poetry platform built for anyone who loves reading and exploring Urdu and Punjabi poetry. It offers a beautiful and easy-to-use interface where you can discover poems by famous poets, search by themes or topics, and even save your favorite pieces. The goal of this project is to create a digital space where poetry lovers can enjoy classic and modern verses in one place.

As a user, you can create your own profile, follow other readers, and build your personal collection of saved poems and poets. You can also view your preferences, explore collections, and take part in community activities. The design of the app is clean and simple, making it easy for everyone to use, whether you're a casual reader or a serious poetry enthusiast.

We’re also planning to add special features like audio versions of poems, where users can listen to poetry being recited. Shehr-e-Sukhan is not just a reading tool — it’s a community where poetry comes alive through sharing, listening, and discovery.
                    </TextBlock>
                </StackPanel>
            </ScrollViewer>
        </Border>

        <!-- Back Button in Bottom-Right Corner -->
        <Button Content="⬅ Back"
                Width="120"
                Height="35"
                HorizontalAlignment="Right"
                VerticalAlignment="Bottom"
                Margin="0,0,20,20"
                Background="#8B0000"
                Foreground="White"
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Click="back_click_about"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>
